content: Data import from Nextcloud to {{organizationName}} {{productName}} is complete!

comment.text: This translation key is used to display a success message after completing data import from Nextcloud to an organization. It appears in the UI as a confirmation message, typically on a button or dialog that indicates successful import completion.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'Входирането' (Vhodirane) isn't the best translation for 'import' in this context. It implies a more formal or bureaucratic import process. A more natural translation for data import would be 'Прехвърлянето' (Prehvarlyane) or 'Импортирането' (Importirane).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Прехвърлянето на данни от Nextcloud към {{organizationName}} {{productName}} приключи!

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'dokončen' while technically correct, might sound slightly formal or bureaucratic in this context. A more natural phrasing would be 'Hotovo!' or 'Ukončený!'
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Import dat z Nextcloudu do {{organizationName}} {{productName}} je Hotovo!

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation uses 'στο {{productName}} του {{organizationName}}' which is a literal translation and sounds awkward in Greek. A more natural phrasing would be 'στο {{productName}} της {{organizationName}}'. While 'του' and 'της' both mean 'of', they are used for masculine and feminine nouns respectively.  {{organizationName}} is likely a feminine noun, so 'της' is more appropriate.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Η εισαγωγή δεδομένων από το Nextcloud στο {{productName}} της {{organizationName}} ολοκληρώθηκε!

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The colon after 'Nextcloudista' creates an awkward reading flow. While grammatically correct, it's not typical in this context and breaks the natural flow of the sentence.

The translation 'ավարտված է' directly translates to 'is finished'. While technically correct, it's less natural in Armenian. A more idiomatic phrasing would be 'կայացել է' which implies successful completion.
The translation uses 'A importação' which is grammatically incorrect. It should be 'A importação de'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: A importação de dados do Nextcloud para o {{organizationName}} {{productName}} está concluída!

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'A importação de dados do Nextcloud para o {{organizationName}} {{productName}} está concluída!' is grammatically correct but slightly awkward. A more natural and common phrasing would be 'A importação de dados do Nextcloud para o {{organizationName}} {{productName}} foi concluída!'
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: A importação de dados do Nextcloud para o {{organizationName}} {{productName}} foi concluída!

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation uses 'date' which means 'day' or 'date' as a noun. 'Import' should be translated to 'Importul' to match the English word.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Importul datelor din Nextcloud în {{organizationName}} {{productName}} este finalizat!

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Serbian translation maintains the English formatting with placeholders {{organizationName}} {{productName}}, which is appropriate.

The phrase "工作区" (gōngzuòqū) which translates to "workspace" is not necessarily accurate for describing a Nextcloud instance. It is not explicitly mentioned in the English text. A more generic term like "Nextcloud" or "来源平台" (láiyuán píngtái - source platform) might be more appropriate.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: 从 Nextcloud 或 来源平台到 {{organizationName}}{{productName}} 的数据导入已完成！
